{
  "stem": "1132.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And my mother was trying to scrounge up food, and the only thing that was available was corn meal.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So she was baking cornmeal, and doing all kinds of things with cornmeal, whatever she could think of to do.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "To this day, I will not eat a corn muffin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I will not eat cornbread.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I will not eat anything that is made of cornmeal in any shape, form.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I just won't touch it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The other thing is that I ate no fish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "I was brought up with no fish in my house after the war, because my mother-- remember, we-- Hungary's is a landlocked country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Landlocked country, no access to the sea.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So there was no seafood.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There is a large lake in the middle of the country, and you will get freshwater fish from there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But much of the fish came what was fished out from the Danube.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And because of the memories associated with the Danube-- that is people being shot in there-- my mother simply could not bring herself to bring in fish into the house.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I grew up having never tasted fish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first time I had fish was in the early '60s when my husband gently started getting me onto trying fish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- we got to the point of me having some fish in restaurants.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I, myself, did not start actually cooking fish until the mid to late '80s, which I think is quite a significant [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] occurrence.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I'm still very careful as to what fish I will eat.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Let's go back to the hiding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was a very strong woman, very strong.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
